{South opens 1\H and North, with 16 points,  responds 2\D, forcing the partnership to game.

South has a minimum strength hand, but with a 6-card suit he rebids 2\H.

Opposite South's 6-card suit, North's doubleton is adequate support. If North had a minimum for her 2/1 response she might just jump to 4\H to show no interest in slam. With a little extra she bids 3\H since she knows the bidding cannot stop until game is reached. From North's perspective South might have a big hand; his 2-level rebid shows suit length but does not say anything about strength. This is one of the beauties of 2/1, the bidding can be kept low while you look for the best place to play. However, this time South merely bids the game and North passes.

The hand would have been bid the same with or without 2/1.}
