{North opens 1\S and South, with 14 points, responds 2\H. Note that South is not permitted to make this bid without a 5-card or longer \H suit.

North, knowing that South has 5, bids 3\H to confirm the trump suit.

South has a minimum strength hand with no slam aspirations, so he uses Fast Arrival and bids 4\H. North is also satisfied to just play at game.

2/1 is a good bidding method, and here, 4\H is a good contract. But you can see that it is not a laydown - there is no bidding system that will always reach T0% contracts. In this hand a 3-3 \D split will provide the Tth trick, or if that fails, taking 2 \S finesses provides a 75% chance of success.}
